{"_path":"/blog/economy-and-analysis-of-economy","_dir":"blog","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"","title":"Economy and Analysis of Economy","description":"","postId":"tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8061911113731935185.post-3336556729413181217","slug":"economy-and-analysis-of-economy","publishedDate":"2008-11-12T05:47:00.000-08:00","layout":"post","body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_UYUaEitRq54/SRrsDg1_-bI/AAAAAAAAAP4/t_zLqrHMju0/s1600-h/DurableVsNonDurable+PPI.jpg","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"2008 saw a great [Financial Crisis.]("},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://www.moolanomy.com/866/what-caused-","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"http://www.moolanomy.com/866/what-caused-"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\nthe-financial-crisis-of-2008/) Not to mention all the commotion, on the future\nof world economy. How did it happen and why wasn't it anticipated? For last\nfew months, I have been talking on the tools to analyse, about the analytics\nand its power to understand the variables and the systems."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_UYUaEitRq54/SRrnJ8z7TpI/AAAAAAAAAPw/k2xakdmqROo/s1600-h/DurableVsNonDurable.jpg","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So, why did such a successful "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Financial_instrument","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"financial\ninstrument"}]},{"type":"text","value":" failed to\nunderstand and predict the impending crisis. It must have been very clear from\nthe numbers. :-)"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"May be it didn't. May be it was just ignored."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Let me choose one basic variables to explain how numbers speak in the world of\neconomics."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"","src":"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_UYUaEitRq54/SRrnJ8z7TpI/AAAAAAAAAPw/k2xakdmqROo/s400/DurableVsNonDurable.jpg"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The above graph shows the relationship between the\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consumer_price_index","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"CPI"}]},{"type":"text","value":" of durables and non-\ndurables goods. Ohh, what is\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consumer_price_index","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"CPI"}]},{"type":"text","value":"? It is simply a\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consumer_price_index","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Consumer Price Index"}]},{"type":"text","value":"- in\nsimple terms it denotes the price of the goods that consumers pay for and is a\ngood indicator for the inflation. So more price means more inflation."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Starting from the early 80s, there is a close call between the price of"},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Durable_good","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\nDurable goods"}]},{"type":"text","value":" (electronic gadgets\netc) and "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Durable_good","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Non-Durable"}]},{"type":"text","value":" (cosmetics,\nfoods etc) goods. The prices seem to be slowly rising. But in 1990, we see the\ndivergence in the price. At around 1997, it seems the price on "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Durable_good","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Durable\ngoods"}]},{"type":"text","value":" are starting to fall very\nslowly, while the price on "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Durable_good","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Non-\nDurable"}]},{"type":"text","value":" goods are shooting high."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now, the analysis is not always about the rise and fall in the numbers. It is\nabout saying why it is happening and how it can be controlled. But before\nthat, let me pose a question. What do you want? Do you want a constant "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consumer_price_index","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"CPI\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"or a rising "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consumer_price_index","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"CPI\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"or a falling\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consumer_price_index","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"CPI"}]},{"type":"text","value":". Which one is better?"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Constant "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consumer_price_index","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"CPI "}]},{"type":"text","value":"would\nobviously denote a stagnant market, with no selling or buying at all.\nInevitably, due to dynamic market , there is always going to be fluctuation.\nSo there is a range in price over which this fluctuation happens. We are\nlooking at a range not at the discrete particular point. But this range also\nincreases and decreases according to civilisation's ability to purchase and\nsell. It like saying what to call expensive and what to call cheap."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So much talk over one graph! Yes, because, one graph is able to give so many\ninformation, because it is affected by many variables which reveals itself on\nthe process of analysis."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now the change in the "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consumer_price_index","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"CPI\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"value of "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Durable_good","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"durable\ngoods"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Durable_good","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"non-durables\ngoods"}]},{"type":"text","value":" can have many reasons. One\nsuch reason can be, the demand of non-durable goods might have increased. Its\na basic economics. Also let me add another graph showing the production cost\nof the "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Durable_good","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Non-durable"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Durable_good","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Durable\ngoods"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"","src":"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_UYUaEitRq54/SRrsDg1_-bI/AAAAAAAAAP4/t_zLqrHMju0/s400/DurableVsNonDurable+PPI.jpg"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We can see that the producer's price index for the "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Durable_good","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Durable\nGoods"}]},{"type":"text","value":" have not changed since 1997\nbut the production cost for the Non-Durable goods have increased at a very\nhigh rate. This may have been reflected on the Consumer's Price Index. But\nthere is a conflict between the correlation of "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consumer_price_index","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"CPI\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"and PPI, which I better\nnot address now."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So, on a simple note changing the production cost changes the consumer's cost.\nIt is not enough, just stating the fact, we still don't know why the\nproduction cost suddenly rose in 1997. Does the "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://www.boostworks.com/?p=133","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Great Asian Crisis on\n1997"}]},{"type":"text","value":" has to do anything with it."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Think about it and let me know what you all think. I may post further articles\ninvestigating this phenomenon."}]}],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[]}},"_type":"markdown","_id":"content:blog:economy-and-analysis-of-economy.md","_source":"content","_file":"blog/economy-and-analysis-of-economy.md","_stem":"blog/economy-and-analysis-of-economy","_extension":"md"}